Interest rates could rise earlier than expected thanks to a growth in employment, putting one million mortgage-holders at risk of losing their homes.

A record 30million people are in work and the trend is set to continue, says the Chartered Institute of Personnel and Development (CIPD).

If unemployment was to fall below 7 per cent, this would prompt the Bank of England to rethink interest rates, governor Mark Carney has said.

