And if rates rise more quickly to 5 per cent by 2018, two million would be tipped into unsustainable levels of debt.

The Resolution Foundation, which based its analysis on Office for Budget Responsibility projections, said: ‘While record low interest rates have reduced current repayment costs, fewer people than we hoped have used this breathing space to pay off their debts.’

